entry.sense:
HaSaI lubaAnK: 
see Ḳ, voce EasalN; 
and see art. HSI.

OaloHaqahu bihi He classed him, as an adjunct, with him; put him on a par with him; or made him to be as though on a par with him; 
See two exs. voce laATa, 
in art. lyT.

laEal-a 
[May-be; perhaps]; a word denoting hope and fear. (Ḳ.) It governs the subject in the accus. case, and the predicate in the nom. See Ibn-ʼAḳeel, ed. of Dieterici, p. 90; 
and see layota.

2. laq-aAhu Xar-FA 
[He made him to experience evil treatment]. (TA in art. jdE, voce jad-aEa.) See below; 
and see mulaq-FI.

Oalamo: 
see the latter half of art. OalaA; 
and the former part of art. OamaA.

layokaA, [i. e. layoka with an adjunct alif for the sake of the rhyme,] 
for Uilayoka: 
see art. UilaI, near the end.

liynapN applied to a palm-tree: 
see art. lwn; 
and see EajowapN.
